cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a new deep learning architecture for stereo disparity estimation, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of an extended cost volume and multiscale contextual information suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The application of the proposed networks to stereo disparity estimation benchmarks suggests a focus on robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM).
